<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1314" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1314">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/731.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s July 23. Department of Hacienda informed me this afternoon
                            that tomorrow recommendation will be made by telegraph permitting the
                            old tax to be effective for the present quarter only, “not because the
                            new rate is unjust but as a temporary concession in view of the
                            circumstances related by the Consul General.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>